(8, NULL, 1, 3, 1, 1, 'Director of IGRMS', 'director-of-igrms', 'Director of IGRMS', 'Director of IGRMS', 'Director of IGRMS', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"height:178.278px; width:205.667px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Prof Amitabh Pande,&nbsp;(Director)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Indira Gandhi Rastriya Manav Sanghralyay, (IGRMS) Bhopal</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Ministry of Culture, Govt of India</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Prof Amitabh Pande is on deputation as Director of Indira Gandhi Rastriya Manav Sanghralyay, Bhopal (Ministry of Culture, Govt of India). He is Professor of Anthropology, Chairperson, International Centre of Community Forestry (ICCF) and Chairperson Training at Indian Institute of Forest Management Bhopal Ministry of Environment and Forest &amp; Climate Change Government of India, prior to joining as Director IGRMS, Bhopal.&nbsp; He is a member of Madhya Pradesh Wetland Authority, Government of Madhya Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dr Amitabh Pande has done PhD in Anthropology from the University of Hyderabad, Hyderabad. He is Environment Anthropologist, with a focused area of research in Cultural conservation, museum science, Public Policy Analysis, Indigenous Knowledge &amp; Biodiversity Conservation, and Collective action in Natural Resource Management. He has expertise in indoor and outdoor museum on sacred groves and indigenous conservation of culture.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>For the past 29 years, he is an active Researcher, Consultant, and Trainer. He has done about 50 research and Consultancy projects, funded by an international and national organisations like&nbsp; World&nbsp; Bank,&nbsp; GIZ,&nbsp; UNDP,&nbsp; UNICEF,&nbsp; JICA,&nbsp; WRI,&nbsp; JSDF,&nbsp; European&nbsp; Union, ICSSR,&nbsp; DST, MOEFCC,&nbsp; MOTA,&nbsp; etc. He&nbsp; has&nbsp; trained&nbsp; senior&nbsp; officers&nbsp; of&nbsp; the&nbsp; SAARC&nbsp; countries&nbsp; (Bhutan&nbsp; and Bangladesh).He&nbsp; has&nbsp; conducted&nbsp; more&nbsp; than&nbsp; 100&nbsp; trainings for international,&nbsp; national&nbsp; and&nbsp; state organisations.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>His recent book is &ldquo;Corporate Biodiversity Management for Sustainable Growth: Assessment of Policies and Action Plans edited book published by Springer Nature. Besides this, he has more than 50 publications in journals, book chapters and reports and four more books to his credit.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>He also had a long sports career and he was University Badminton Champion from 1988-92 and&nbsp; had&nbsp; led&nbsp; Hyderabad&nbsp; University&nbsp; Badminton&nbsp; and&nbsp; Cricket&nbsp; team&nbsp; in&nbsp; the&nbsp; All&nbsp; India&nbsp; Inter- University Games and IIFM team in the All India Forest Meet held annually. He loves horse riding and mountaineering.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Contact No. 09425017945&nbsp;(Whatsapp and call),&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Email - dirigrms-mp[at]nic[dot]in/amitabhpandey67[at]gmail[dot]com</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, 4, 0, 'Director of IGRMS', '2023-09-20 04:30:29', '2025-04-30 04:56:43');
