(195, NULL, 1, 7, 1, 1, 'Southern Regional Centre Mysuru', 'southern-regional-centre-mysuru', 'Southern Regional Centre Mysuru', 'Southern Regional Centre Mysore', 'Southern Regional Centre Mysore', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The Southern Regional Centre of Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya (IGRMS) at Mysuru is the outcome of initiatives of the central government and the State Government of Karnataka. The Government of Karnataka had allotted in a State protected monument &lsquo;Wellington House&rsquo; at Mysore, a small indoor accommodation (measuring: 672.44 sqm) and its surrounding open areas (measuring: 5518.74 sq.mt) in the year 2000 to establish the Regional Centre of IGRMS on a lease basis for 33 years. A Memorandum of Understanding was formalized in March, 2000 and possession of the said accommodation was taken over the IGRMS. This building has an historical account which was earlier occupied by the Duke of Wellington (1799-1801 A. D). The Government of Karnataka has declared the Wellington Lodge as a State Protected in the year 1981 under the provisions of the Karnataka Ancient and Historical Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains Act 1961.The Southern Regional Centre started functioning from 2001 onwards.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Since its inception, the Southern Regional Centre, had organized large scale inter-regional cultural exchange programmes of communities, &lsquo;Do and Learn&rsquo; Museum Education programmes, artisan&rsquo;s workshops, and performing arts presentation to revitalize the vanishing aspects of valuable traditional art and craft forms.&nbsp; Besides, various collaborative activities with universities, research institutes, and museums are also organized from time to time. Several periodical thematic exhibitions are organized based on regional cultures and various subject matters related to Anthropology, Archaeology, Environment and other related disciplines. In addition, various artists / artisan groups from different parts of India are encouraged to showcase and demonstrate the aesthetic beauties of their art, craft through in campus and outreach activities to promote national integration. The Southern Regional Centre so far has made a valuable collection from the states of Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala, Tamilnadu, Telangana and Lakshadweep Islands.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pSouthern Regional Centre Mysore/p', '2024-12-10 02:53:02', '2025-04-04 06:13:21'),
(196, NULL, 1, 7, 1, 1, 'Cultural Interpretation Centres', 'cultural-interpretation-centres', 'Cultural Interpretation Centres', 'Cultural Interpretation Centres', 'Cultural Interpretation Centres', '<p>The Cultural Interpreter Centre aims to expand the activities of the Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya (IGRMS) to diverse regions across the country. These centres will foster a network of collaborative relationships with local communities and their associations.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pCultural Interpretation Centres/p', '2024-12-10 02:54:15', '2025-01-31 01:16:29'),
