(264, NULL, 1, 263, 1, 1, 'Artists Workshops', 'artists-workshops', 'Artists Workshops', 'Artists Workshops', 'Artists Workshops', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Creation of craft items or artifacts among folk and tribal communities is not only a medium of livelihood but also contains socio-religious significance and aesthetic sense of respective artisan community. These art forms evolved in time and space have been an identity marker of a region or a community residing there. Although being tangible in their appearance such art traditions contain several intangible aspects important for the study of various ethnic groups and their interrelations. With an aim to document various art traditions, artisans as well as to enrich museum&rsquo;s collection, as also to provide an opportunity of direct interaction between artisans and visitors at same place IGRMS organizes artists camps and workshops in various parts of the country and its headquarters at Bhopal and Southern Regional Centre at Mysore.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pArtists Workshops/p', '2024-12-10 05:14:11', '2024-12-31 02:21:01'),
(265, NULL, 1, 263, 1, 1, 'Performing art presentation', 'performing-art-presentation', 'Performing art presentation', 'Performing art presentation', 'Performing art presentation', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/Performing art presentation -2_1739603286.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dance and music play a vital role in human life, particularly in folk and tribal societies, where they are deeply ingrained in the culture. Music, in its diverse forms, serves as a powerful medium for communication, expression of emotions, and education. As an effort to bring the museum experience to local communities and promote national unity, IGRMS arranges live performances of folk, tribal, and classical music, as well as theatrical presentations. These initiatives are invaluable for fostering cultural understanding among people from different regions and contribute significantly to the burgeoning museum movement in the country.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pPerforming art presentation/p', '2024-12-10 05:15:01', '2025-02-15 01:38:18'),
(266, NULL, 1, 263, 1, 1, 'Poonam', 'poonam', 'Poonam', 'Poonam', 'Poonam', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Poonam is a well-received series at the IGRMS, showcasing classical music and dance performances by nationally and internationally acclaimed artists. These events take place in the museum&#39;s open-air auditorium on full moon nights. The series started in the early 90s as an experiment to introduce world-famous classical performers to a general audience and music lovers in an informal and enchanting natural setting in the hills.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>So far 38 episodes have been commenced and artist like Subha Mudgal, Bheem Sen Joshi, Pandit Jasraj, Shiv Kumar Sharma, Pandit Hari Prasad Chaurasia and many more gems of Indian classical traditions have grace the stage.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pPoonam/p', '2024-12-10 05:15:58', '2024-12-31 02:22:45'),
(267, NULL, 1, 263, 1, 1, 'Do  Learn Museum Education Program', 'do-learn-museum-education-program', 'Do  Learn Museum Education Program', 'Do  Learn Museum Education Program', 'Do  Learn Museum Education Program', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The Museum organises demonstration and training programmes for registered participants under the activity by inviting tribal and rural artists and artisans from various domains of the creativity, and knowledge systems.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pDo amp Learn Museum Education Program/p', '2024-12-10 05:17:14', '2024-12-31 02:27:57'),
(268, NULL, 1, 263, 1, 1, 'Seminars and Academic Workshops', 'seminars-and-academic-workshops', 'Seminars and Academic Workshops', 'Seminars and Academic Workshops', 'Seminars and Academic Workshops', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The Museum organizes seminars, webinars, symposiums, colloquiums, workshops on various themes associated with Museum, Anthropology and its allied disciplines. These events provides an opportunity to engage with experts and gain deeper insights into the subjects. Participants can also network with like-minded individuals, fostering collaborations and professional growth. Additionally, these events offer a platform to stay updated with the latest research and trends in the field.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pSeminars and Academic Workshopsnbsp/p', '2024-12-10 05:18:24', '2024-12-31 02:28:33');
