(332, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Agriculture', 'agriculture', 'Agriculture', 'Agriculture', 'Agriculture', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/AG 5_1739596020.JPG\" style=\"height:386px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>IGRMS has collected different types of agricultural implements which include, sickle, hoe-cum-spade, plough &amp; yoke, digging stick, spade, straw separating stick, seed funnel etc. mainly from Meghalaya, Assam, Orissa, Uttar Pradesh, Gujarat, Rajasthan, Andhra Pradesh and Tamil Nadu being used by various tribal and non-tribal communities of India. These implements are mainly collected from the Korku, Gaddi, Warli, Jounsari, Agaria, Lepcha, Rabari, Bondo and Kota tribes.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pAgriculture/p', '2025-02-10 07:17:43', '2025-02-14 23:37:16'),
(333, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Animal Husbandry', 'animal-husbandry', 'Animal Husbandry', 'Animal Husbandry', 'Animal Husbandry', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/AH 1_1739596119.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The implements related to animal husbandry are collected from Gujarat, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Tamil Nadu etc. used mainly by the Rabari, Lohar, Birhor and Gond people. The collected articles include decoration for camel, copper bell, bark rope to tie the animal, white rope for cattle, feeding trough, ornament for buffalo, disk for buffalo ornamentation, brass bell for cattle, seat decoration on camel&rsquo;s back, copper bell for cattle, nose top for camel etc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pAnimal Husbandry/p', '2025-02-11 00:08:59', '2025-02-14 23:38:56'),
(334, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Art and Craft', 'art-and-craft', 'Art and Craft', 'Art and Craft', 'Art and Craft', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/AC 5_1739596291.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The function of art and craft in providing a livelihood is often surpassed by its more important function on the major events of life such as birth, initiation marriage, death as well as annual and seasonal festival. Therefore, most of the objects include in this category are terracotta, paintings, wooden or metal objects which are integral part of socio-religious order of traditional and contemporary village and tribal India. In this category IGRMS has collected various creative objects in different forms and mediums which includes terracotta, wood, grass, shells, iron, bell metal and paintings.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pArt and Craft/p', '2025-02-11 00:16:33', '2025-02-14 23:42:09'),
(335, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Basketry', 'basketry', 'Basketry', 'Basketry', 'Basketry', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/B1_1739596392.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>It is an art of using two connected elements, the wrap and the weft to make an object. A basket differs from an object made by felting in having interlaced materials. The coiled basketry, plaited (hand-woven) basketry and twined basketry are the three important forms of basketry. IGRMS has collected basket with lid, carrying basket, fish basket, shallow basket, bamboo basket etc. form Uttar Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Meghalaya, Maharashtra, Orissa, Tamil Nadu, Gujarat, Kerala, Bihar which are used by the Khasi, Bhil, Warli, Agaria, Toda, Bondo, Oraon, Abujh Maria, Kota, Baiga, Rathwa was tribes for various purposes.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pBasketry/p', '2025-02-11 00:18:00', '2025-02-14 23:43:27'),
(336, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Fishing', 'fishing', 'Fishing', 'Fishing', 'Fishing', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/F 4_1739596573.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>In India fishing is a very important source of livelihood particularly among the tribal and rural communities. There are a number of communities in India depending upon the fishing economy whose major occupation is fishing and selling the fish in the market. Because of their occupation they are known as &lsquo;Fishermen&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Other than the fishermen there are certain communities who practice fishing as the secondary resources of this economy where as some practice is as time pass or enjoyment. The river, canals, ponds, dams, sea etc. are the various sources where the fishing is practiced. Depending upon the location and nature of water there are different types of fishing implements used. IGRMS has collected different types of fishing implements which include nets, traps, harpoons, spear, hooks etc. from various parts of India.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pFishing/p', '2025-02-11 00:18:47', '2025-02-14 23:46:27');
