(337, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Games And Amusement', 'games-and-amusement', 'Games And Amusement', 'Games And Amusement', 'Games And Amusement', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/GA 7_1739596647.jpg\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Games and amusements play an important role in the life of the people. One can observe various types of games and amusements in different parts of the country. Some games are found every where in the country where as some games are region, occasion, age, sex and community specific. Whatever be the means of games and amusements, it has socio-cultural significance and serves some social and religious purposes. In this category IGRMS has collected objects from different means of amusement found in traditional as well as contemporary culture which includes masks, toys, puppetry, dices, tops, leather puppet and dolls.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pGames amp Amusement/p', '2025-02-11 00:19:43', '2025-02-14 23:47:42'),
(338, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Household', 'household', 'Household', 'Household', 'Household', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/HH 1_1739596731.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Household articles are very common objects found in each and every family, society and culture. In this category the objects are strongly related to the food quest of man. From cooking utensils of the kitchen to the granary and from sitting objects to sleeping peripherals all are included in this category. There is a large collection of household objects present in IGRMS archive which are collected from different corners of the country. The main objects in this category includes utensils, plates, glass, pitchers, grinders, mate, containers, brooms, lamps etc. which are made of different materials like clay, wood, brass, leaf and metals.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pHousehold/p', '2025-02-11 00:20:22', '2025-02-14 23:49:04'),
(339, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Hunting', 'hunting', 'Hunting', 'Hunting', 'Hunting', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/Hu 4_1739596808.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The IGRMS has collected many objects in this category from different groups or communities as well as regions. Nets, traps, bow and arrow, gum sticks, spear, cage etc. are some important hunting implements collected by the IGRMS officials from different parts of the country.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pHunting/p', '2025-02-11 00:20:56', '2025-02-14 23:50:23'),
(340, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Musical', 'collection-musical', 'Musical', 'Musical', 'Musical', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/Mu 5_1739596899.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>IGRMS has a large number of collections in this category. On the basis of typology, shape, size and use these musical instruments are categorized into four groups, such as percussion instrument, string instrument, wind instrument and clapper groups. The <em>Percussion instrument</em>&nbsp; includes single and double membrane drums, Tambourine where as the <em>String instruments </em>&nbsp;include Violin, Sitar, Musical bow etc. In the <em>Wind instrument</em> flutes Whistles, blowing pipes and bugles are important. The <em>Clapper</em> group includes cymbals, gongs and musical bells are important.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pMusical/p', '2025-02-11 00:21:34', '2025-02-14 23:51:53'),
(341, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Narcotics', 'narcotics', 'Narcotics', 'Narcotics', 'Narcotics', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/N 1_1739596979.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:859px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The use of tobacco, alcohols and other means of narcotics are characterized as the leisure time pass by some communities on one hand where as on the other hand they are the essential part of important ritual ceremonies. In India, particularly among the tribal, the offering of tobacco and alcohols to the guest is very much regarded a respectful practice for the guest. The objects included in this category are Tobacco pouches, Lime and Betel leaf containers, Areca nut Crackers, Chilams, Pipes, Hookkas, Alcohol containers, serving ladles etc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pNarcotics/p', '2025-02-11 00:23:22', '2025-02-14 23:53:12'),
(342, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Ornament', 'ornament', 'Ornament', 'Ornament', 'Ornament', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/O2_1739597072.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Among the folk and tribal communities of our country the jewellary or ornaments are believed to possess attributes of protecting the wearer from evil spirits and thus are not mere articles of adornments. This collection reflects the immense variety of folk and tribal jewellery of India, both in terms of materials used, which include lac, glass, shells, grass, threads, beads, feathers, bones, silver, copper, bronze etc. as well as in particular tradition in wearing. IGRMS has a good collection of ornaments from different parts of the country made of different materials.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pOrnament/p', '2025-02-11 00:23:57', '2025-02-14 23:54:55'),
(343, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Ritual', 'collection-ritual', 'Ritual', 'Ritual', 'Ritual', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/R 3_1739597178.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Study and documentations of any community or culture is not possible without understanding their belief system. Each and every individual believes in some kind of supernatural power. Whatever the society is, weather nature worshiper or idol worshiper, different types of ritual articles would be required. IGRMS has collected a number of objects related to worship magical practices, offerings and other ritual articles. This collection includes the idols, statues, images, offerings and other objects of ritual importance.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pRitual/p', '2025-02-11 00:24:38', '2025-02-14 23:56:32'),
(344, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Spinning  And Weaving', 'spinning-and-weaving', 'Spinning  And Weaving', 'Spinning  Weaving', 'Spinning  Weaving', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/SW 2_1739597401.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Spinning means making yarn out of fiber through lengthening and twisting it where as weaving is a technique for making cloth for cordage. The materials used are softer and narrower than in basketry and are worked on a loom. Weaving involves interlacing two series of phi-able elements at right angles to each other. IGRMS has collected bucket for loom, loin loom with accessories, wooden tool for weaving, loin loom, spinning article used for embroidering in weaving, spinning wheel, spindle etc. from Manipur, Uttar Pradesh, Orissa, Assam, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh used by the different tribal groups.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pSpinning amp Weaving/p', '2025-02-11 00:25:38', '2025-02-15 00:00:15'),
(345, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Textile, Dress and Costume', 'textile-dress-and-costume', 'Textile, Dress and Costume', 'Textile, Dress and Costume', 'Textile, Dress and Costume', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/T 5_1739597483.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Depending upon the climatic condition and the geomorphological location of the area, people of India use various kinds of costume in different parts of the country. Some time a person changes his costumes according to the occasion (marriage, festival etc.), availability, place and time of use. Other than the wearing there are different types of textiles used for different purposes. Because of their ritual or social signification this costumes are required to be preserved. IGRMS has collected different varieties of costumes for different age and sex groups from different regions and community of India. Other than costumes IGRMS has also collected some embroidered, dyed, printed, hand woven and fabricated clothes like Kantha, Kalamkari, Pichhavais, Alizarine, Phulkari, Chickenkari, etc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pTextile, Dress and Costume/p', '2025-02-11 00:26:53', '2025-02-15 00:01:35'),
(346, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Tools', 'tools', 'Tools', 'Tools', 'Tools', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/To 7_1739597577.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Tools are the instruments used by man for solving different domestic purposes. IGRMS has collected hammer, iron tongs, spade, chisel, match lock, a wood chopping tool, anvil, a fire making device, toddy tapping tool, oil crusher, adze, axe, rope weaving, mango cutting tool, sugar-cane crusher, cutting tool, iron forceps, bamboo splitting tool, iron knife etc. from Maharashtra, Uttar Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Assam, Tamil Nadu and other states of India which are used by the Khasi, Warli, Jounsari, Gond, Korku, Toda, Kota, Agaria and Chenchu tribes.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pTools/p', '2025-02-11 00:27:30', '2025-02-15 00:03:10'),
(347, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Travel And Transport', 'travel-and-transport', 'Travel And Transport', 'Travel  Transport', 'Travel  Transport', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/TT 3_1739597653.tif\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/TT 2_1739597815.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>IGRMS has collected different means of Travel and Transport used in tribal and folk societies of India. Some of these traditional means of transportations are still used in the rural areas.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The IGRMS has collected such kind of traditional transporting instruments from different parts of the country which includes bullock carts, boats, floating instrument, palanquin etc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pTravel amp Transport/p', '2025-02-11 00:28:08', '2025-02-15 00:07:22'),
(348, NULL, 1, 297, 1, 1, 'Weapons', 'weapons', 'Weapons', 'Weapons', 'Weapons', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://125.20.102.85/igrms/public/upload/files/W 2_1739597888.JPG\" style=\"height:370px; width:850px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Weapons are used either for offence or defense purpose. Iron knife, spear, bent bladed cutting tool, knife, battle axe, iron shield are some of the major weapons collected by IGRMS from different tribal and non tribal communities residing in various parts of the country. Out of the total collection, the maximum numbers of weapons are collected from the Muria, Saora, Toda, Bondo, Kota, and Gadaba etc. tribes residing in Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Orissa, Assam, Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Kerala, Bihar and Manipur.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 4, NULL, 0, 'pWeapons/p', '2025-02-11 00:28:44', '2025-02-15 00:08:21'),
